magicbook.gtlitecore.api.utils.maps

接口 SequencedSet<E>

  • 类型参数:
    E -
    所有超级接口:
    java.util.Collection<E>, java.lang.Iterable<E>, SequencedCollection<E>, java.util.Set<E>

    public interface SequencedSet<E>
extends SequencedCollection<E>, java.util.Set<E>
    A collection that is both a SequencedCollection and a Set. As such, it can be thought of either as a Set that also has a well-defined encounter order, or as a SequencedCollection that also has unique elements.

    This interface has the same requirements on the equals and hashCode methods as defined by Set.equals(java.lang.Object) and Set.hashCode(). Thus, a Set and a SequencedSet will compare equals if and only if they have equal elements, irrespective of ordering.

    A SequencedSet defines the reversed() method, which provides a reverse-ordered view of this set. The only difference from the SequencedCollection.reversed() method is that the return type of reversed() is SequencedSet.

    This class is the port of Java 21 Feature "Sequenced Collection", in Java 21, some sets like SortedSet extends this class, but we cannot let them extends this class yet, so we add some utils sequenced sets.

      • reversed

        SequencedSet<E> reversed()
        Returns a reverse-ordered view of this collection. The encounter order of elements in the returned view is the inverse of the encounter order of elements in this collection. The reverse ordering affects all order-sensitive operations, including those on the view collections of the returned view. If the collection implementation permits modifications to this view, the modifications "write through" to the underlying collection. Changes to the underlying collection might or might not be visible in this reversed view, depending upon the implementation.
        指定者:
        reversed 在接口中 SequencedCollection<E>
        返回:
        A reverse-ordered view of this collection, as a SequencedSet.
        另请参阅:
        SequencedCollection.reversed()
